Teach, Experiment, Create, Help: The foundations of the T.E.C.H. club. Many students have some technology related ability or talent. We, as club organizers, push such students to share and TEACH their skills to others. To solidify and ingrain these newly learnt skills, we EXPERIMENT with the information by creatively exploring the world of technology (drones, coding, computer repair, graphic design, modeling, robots, etc.). Finally, the club body can create world changing applications stemming from learnt skills, all in independently formed groups. We host an exposition to show off the creations and fundraise for future activities. In addition, the T.E.C.H club prides itself in helping the community. Some of our goals include spreading computer science education to schools in need (our student taught lessons will be published to the app) and assisting those in Ridgefield High School who have tech problems that must be solved. \nThe T.E.C.H club is fitting for all, and we hope to see you at our next meeting.
